-- Intelligence Agencies Intercept Plans for U.K. Terror Plot, Sky TV Reports
-- B y   B e n   L i v e s e y
-- 2010-09-28T21:08:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/intelligence-agencies-intercept-plans-for-u-k-terror-plot-sky-reports.html
Intelligence agencies intercepted a
terror plot targeting London and other cities in the U.K, Sky
News reported, citing unnamed sources.    The plot, by militants based in Pakistan, was at an
“advanced but not imminent stage” and had been tracked by spy
agencies “for some time,” Sky said.   Similar attacks targeting France and Germany were also
planned, Sky said.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Livesey at 
 blivesey@bloomberg.net  